<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="460" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,438,1039]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,438,463]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male. In the group VIII key of 
<bibRefCitation author="Borgmeier" box="[652,858,438,463]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" refString="Borgmeier, T. (1966) Revision of the North American phorid flies. Part III. The species of the genus Megaselia, subgenus Megaselia. Studia Entomologica, 8, 1 - 160." type="journal article" year="1966">
Borgmeier (
<number box="[790,850,438,463]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" value="1966.0">1966</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[873,998,438,462]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fujiokai">
<emphasis box="[873,998,438,462]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">M. fujiokai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
keys to 
<taxonomicName authority="Borgmeier" authorityName="Borgmeier" box="[1102,1371,438,463]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seticerca">
<emphasis box="[1102,1242,439,462]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">M. seticerca</emphasis>
Borgmeier
</taxonomicName>
from which it differs in numerous ways. Most easily, 
<taxonomicName box="[741,871,475,499]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fujiokai">
<emphasis box="[741,871,475,499]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">M. fujiokai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a large, spheroid epandrium with medium hypoproct hairs (
<figureCitation box="[345,428,510,535]" captionStart="FIGURES 69 – 74" captionStartId="25.[151,264,1914,1937]" captionTargetBox="[168,1425,262,1848]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[151,1435,247,1863]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 69 – 74. Male genitalia, left lateral. 69. Megaselia defibaughorum. 70. Megaselia donahuei. 71. Megaselia francoae. 72. Megaselia fujiokai. 73. Megaselia hardingorum. 74. Megaselia heini." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242985/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">
Fig. 
<number box="[399,428,511,535]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" value="72.0">72</number>
</figureCitation>
) in contrast to the medium sized epadrium with minute hypoproct hairs of 
<taxonomicName box="[1290,1429,511,534]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seticerca">
<emphasis box="[1290,1429,511,534]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">M. seticerca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Additionally, 
<taxonomicName box="[304,427,547,571]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fujiokai">
<emphasis box="[304,427,547,571]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">M. fujiokai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has 
<number box="[478,492,547,571]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" value="4.0">4</number>
alular setae compared to the 
<number box="[821,835,547,571]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" value="3.0">3</number>
on 
<taxonomicName box="[877,1014,547,570]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seticerca">
<emphasis box="[877,1014,547,570]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">M. seticerca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1029,1114,546,571]" captionStart="FIGURES 33 – 42" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1863,1886]" captionTargetBox="[180,1416,264,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,251,1820]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 33 – 42. Right wing, dorsal. 33. Megaselia armstrongorum. 34. Megaselia bradyi. 35. Megaselia brejchaorum. 36. Megaselia carthayensis. 37. Megaselia ciancii. 38. Megaselia creasoni. 39. Megaselia defibaughorum. 40. Megaselia donahuei. 41. Megaselia francoae. 42. Megaselia fujiokai." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242981/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">
Fig. 
<number box="[1082,1114,547,571]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" value="42.0">42</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
